window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p>An ill wind blows from the South....</p> <p>As corruption seeps from the southern kingdom of Nanyue, Wu Ying sets out on a dangerous journey to uncover its source. Spirit stones have become corrupted, with twisted daos embedded within. If left unchecked, this corruption threatens to spread across the world.</p> <p>With the guidance of the wind of heaven, Wu Ying travels across the exotic kingdom where he must confront powerful daos and perilous threats. Along the way, he is aided by companions new and old as he battles to stop the corruption before it is too late.<br> <br> <i>The Third Cut</i> is book nine of the xianxia cultivation series <i>A Thousand Li</i>. The series is about immortal cultivation, wondrous martial art styles, and spirit beasts, which will be loved by wuxia and xianxia fans. <i>The Third Cut</i> is written by Tao Wong, the best-selling scifi and fantasy LitRPG author of the <i>System Apocalypse, Adventures on Brad, </i>and the<i> Hidden Wishes</i>.</p>"; 
